2500|$|Le Fanu, his works, and {{his family}} {{background}} are explored in Gavin Selerie's mixed prose/verse text Le Fanu's Ghost (2006). Gary William Crawford's J. Sheridan Le Fanu: A Bio-Bibliography (1995) is the first full bibliography. Crawford and Brian J. Showers's Joseph Sheridan Le Fanu: A Concise Bibliography (2011) is a supplement to Crawford's out-of-print 1995 bibliography. With Jim Rockhill and Brian J. Showers, Crawford has edited Reflections in a Glass Darkly: Essays on J. Sheridan Le Fanu. Jim Rockhill's introductions to the three volumes of the <b>Ash-Tree</b> Press edition of Le Fanu's short supernatural fiction (Schalken the Painter and Others , The Haunted Baronet and Others , Mr Justice Harbottle and Others [...] ) provide a perceptive account of Le Fanu's life and work.|$|E
