5000|$|The name Ashford {{derives from}} the Old English æsc and ford, and means a ford where <b>ash-trees</b> grow. In 926 the village was known as Æscforda and in the Domesday Book of 1086 it was Aisseford. The {{addition}} of [...] "in-the-Water" [...] occurred in the late 17th century, and reflected {{the proximity of the}} village to meanders of the River Wye.|$|R
