60|$|A deep glen, {{where the}} light was subdued and the colors dim, cleft the mountain's {{northern}} flank, and at its mouth a cluster of white houses stood among the trees; then, on a narrow green level, bright in the sun, the old abbey shone rosy red. Ancient <b>ash-trees</b> and crumbling granite walls straggled about it, but the molding of the high, east window, buttress and tower, still rose in lines of beauty, worked in warm-colored stone.|$|R
